{
  "stem": "22685.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then we went to Stalingrad with that barge.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But before we went to Stalingrad, before we arrived to Stalingrad, the barge stopped in a little town-- a little village.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we walked into the store of the village, and the manager of the store happened to be Jewish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We told him what-- what we are doing, where we want to go.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He said, don't go to Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Stop before Stalingrad, because everything is going-- all the transportation is organized before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we stopped before Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we did-- the transporter was still empty, and we were the first in that-- we had half of it was a cattle wagons-- half and then three families from Odessa, Jewish families just happened to be-- came in in Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we, for three months, took us to go from Stalingrad to Asia, which usually is a trip of a day or something.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But it was war, and all kinds of things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And every transport had priority on our transport.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this way we arrived to Tashkent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1940-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] '41, but in November or December.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then from there again, they took us to a kolkhoz to work-- about south of Bukhara, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mentioned Bukhara because it was the famous Jewish musical, and a well-known Jewish community, which had lived in Bukhara.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many of them, or most of them, had been to Palestine at that time before the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we stayed in that kolkhoz, and the name of the kolkhoz was [NON-ENGLISH], which doesn't mean anything.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And until the Germans were beaten in Stalingrad, and they started to retreat, then we decided to come-- to go closer home-- from-- to travel to-- back to-- to Russia.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
